For the analysis point of view, the power losses are ignored. For the reason that both converters are boost type, it is assumed that the capacitor voltages VC1 and VC2 are larger than the input voltage VS. Also, both converters have equal duty cycles, the same value of inductances, and the output voltage for each converter has the same average value.9D1=D2=D;L1=L2=L;VC1=VC2=VC.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
